			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Puretone and how do you use it?<a name="27283"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 12 04 12:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Information flood time....
<br />

<br />
If you will notice, your 'disc's are now on different timers. Any old info you might see will tell you that it was either deftdance or puretone, then you were without for about an hour.
<br />

<br />
Now you can pop deftdance and as soon as its done pop puretone.  There is even a status bar kinda like the casting bar in the new UI window that shows relative time expired and remaining. If you try to pop a disc and its timer hasn't run, you get a message on the time left before its available again. 
<br />

<br />
In addition, if you are in the middle of puretone and the crap hits the fan you can pop deftdance (it will cancel the puretone but give you a full run of deftdance).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
