				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Puretone and how do you use it?<a name="27447"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 13 04 1:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For instance times to puretone...
<br />

<br />
--Beginning of a Named dragon (or an raid major Named) kill, or just shortly in
<br />

<br />
--Beginning of a boss/mini boss mob fight (LDoN or otherwise)
<br />

<br />
--When the crap hits the fan and you need that extra oomph, (if you are not aggroed...if aggroed, it may be a deftdance moment)
<br />

<br />

<br />
--When time is getting critical in an Adventure, or you are nearing the end and just want to add some punch.
<br />

<br />
etc
<br />

<br />
I always hated, on a raid, sitting in PoK at my bind point listening to the play-by-play in guild chat and seeing Puretone still available...so I started doing it early rather than late.
<br />

<br />
As stated before, it used be many folks would hold off on puretone because they were afraid they might need a deftdance....with the separate timers, thats not a consideration any more.
<br />

<br />
Remember it may give you a few more options (especially if non-epiced) on weapon choices, since you don't nead an instrument/weaponstrument equipped for, say, the AE resist songs. Laggin in raids can make instrument swapping a bit of a problem.  You may even choose to add a little dps with melee against a raid target, especially if you can swap in a hate reducing weapon (and not fear aggro so much--such as the disembowler).
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
